## 1. Operating posture

### 1.1 KFM governing rules applied to Anderson County

| Rule | Anderson County application |
|---|---|
| EvidenceBundle outranks generated language. | Public text about Anderson County must trace to official or admitted EvidenceBundles before publication. Generated narrative can draft, but cannot certify. |
| Public clients use governed APIs and released artifacts. | Focus Mode, map layers, Evidence Drawer, and any public UI must consume governed response envelopes, released artifacts, catalog/triplet/graph records, and policy-safe tile services only. |
| Public UI must not read RAW, WORK, QUARANTINE, unpublished candidates, restricted sources, canonical stores, or model runtime output. | Anderson County county/city web captures, property-service references, road layers, floodplain layers, and recreation candidates remain blocked from public display until processed, cataloged, reviewed, and released. |
| Publication is a governed state transition, not a file move. | Moving a Markdown file into `docs/` does not publish Anderson County Focus Mode. Release requires manifest, evidence closure, policy decision, review state, correction path, and rollback target. |
| Source roles remain distinct. | County government web, city web, Census statistics, KDOT transportation, KDWP recreation, KSHS history, NASS agriculture, FEMA floodplain, and generated narrative stay separate. |
| Cite-or-abstain. | If the system cannot prove a county claim with admissible evidence, it returns `ABSTAIN`, not a guessed answer. |
| Sensitive and risky content fails closed. | Parcel title, living-person profiles, exact vulnerable locations, emergency operations, public-safety tactics, critical infrastructure exposure, and live safety guidance are denied by default. |

