### 2.4 Distinct series value

Anderson County adds a governance-heavy public-web and civic-service proof slice. Many county plans emphasize hydrology, geology, reservoirs, archaeology, or rare ecology. Anderson’s strongest contribution is different: it is a clean test of how KFM handles **official local-government pages that are useful to the public but explicitly not substitutes for official records or legal authority**. That makes Anderson an ideal place to prove official-authority redirects, property/legal abstention behavior, and county/city source-role separation.

### 2.5 Public benefit

A safe Anderson County Focus Mode would help a public user understand:

- where official county and city sources exist;
- which source can support which type of claim;
- how to distinguish “public convenience web information” from legal reliance;
- how to explore high-level county/city, working-landscape, recreation, transport, and history context without exposing sensitive or legally risky details;
- when KFM refuses, abstains, or redirects to an official authority.

