## 3. Product thesis

### 3.1 One-sentence thesis

**Anderson County Focus Mode should make local-government, municipal, working-landscape, recreation, transportation, and history context intelligible through evidence-backed map and answer surfaces while refusing to become a title/access, zoning/legal, emergency, live-safety, infrastructure-vulnerability, or sensitive-location system.**

### 3.2 First-product promises

| Promise | Boundary |
|---|---|
| Show public-safe county/city source anchors. | Only source role, citation, currentness, and official-authority redirect are shown. |
| Explain what a source can and cannot prove. | Does not substitute for county records, city legal determinations, emergency channels, or source agencies. |
| Provide high-level Anderson County map context. | Uses governed APIs and released artifacts only. |
| Use Evidence Drawer for every consequential claim. | EvidenceRef must resolve to EvidenceBundle before public answer. |
| Demonstrate denial and abstention behavior. | Denials and abstentions are first-class outcomes, not UI failures. |
| Prepare for later NASS/Census/KDWP/KSHS/KDOT/FEMA/KGS integration. | Candidate sources require rights, currentness, geometry, sensitivity, and source-role admission. |

### 3.3 Explicit non-promises

| Non-promise | Reason |
|---|---|
| No title, deed, ownership, property-access, or parcel-boundary truth. | Property-service web visibility is not legal title or access authority. |
| No zoning/legal/compliance decisions. | City/county web pages do not make KFM a legal authority. |
| No live emergency, law-enforcement, road-closure, facility, or trail safety guidance. | KFM is not an emergency alert or operational command system. |
| No exact vulnerable infrastructure or sensitive ecology/culture/archaeology locations. | Sensitive locations fail closed. |
| No private-well, water-right, potability, or individualized environmental-health conclusions. | Scientific/administrative data does not become property-level or health advice. |
| No publication merely because files exist in `docs/`. | Promotion is governed state transition, not file placement. |

