## 14. Risk register

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Required mitigation | Release posture |
|---|---:|---:|---|---|
| County web treated as legal authority. | High | High | Boundary banner, official-record redirect, legal-reliance fixture. | Block release until deny/redirect tested. |
| Property-service pages become title/access or living-person profiles. | High | High | Deny property/title/access requests; no parcel/living-person profile in public slice. | Block. |
| City code/zoning context becomes legal/compliance decision. | Medium | High | Source-role anti-collapse; legal/zoning denial fixtures. | Block. |
| Emergency/public-safety pages become live guidance. | Medium | High | Operational-public-safety deny policy. | Block. |
| Trail/recreation context becomes live safety or closure advice. | Medium | Medium-High | Current official notice requirement; abstain when missing. | Block live-status claims. |
| Candidate sources used before admission. | Medium | High | Candidate-source status, source-admission checklist, release gate. | Block. |
| Public visibility mistaken for redistribution rights. | Medium | High | Rights review, metadata-only mode when uncertain. | Block derivative display. |
| Sensitive locations exposed. | Medium | High | Generalization/redaction and exact-location denial. | Block. |
| Aggregate data used for property/health/water-right claims. | Medium | High | Aggregate-only labels and deny/abstain rules. | Block. |
| Stale pages produce outdated guidance. | Medium | Medium | Checked dates, stale-after policy, currentness panel. | Restrict or abstain. |
| Repository path drift creates parallel authority. | Medium | Medium | Directory Rules review and ADR/drift register if divergent. | Block merge if unresolved. |
| Release without rollback. | Low-Med | High | ReleaseManifest + RollbackPlan required. | Block publication. |

